{"build_type":"library","description":"Replay requester: woken by the fault-journal doorbell, reads the last FAULT record's binary name, looks up the registered collector state at the error-ring rendezvous, reserves the trace ring, spawns the crash-log decoder, finds the faulted binary's work-item index, marks state[8]=index+1 and rings the collector doorbell so the collector re-dispatches that item under trace. Event-driven, tail-recursive. [PATCH: wait on the error-ring via broadcast (await-ring-broadcast-event) so this reader is never starved by the other consumer.]","module_name":"drive-trace-replay-requests-from-fault-journal","package_name":"drive-trace-replay-requests-from-fault-journal","function_definitions":{"drive-trace-replay-requests-from-fault-journal":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"context","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"ebase","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":105553116266496},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"edoor","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":105553116266520},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"rend","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":105553116266544},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"z","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"mask","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1023},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"hdr","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":64},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"recsz","variabl